==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Witticism
<hw>Wit"ti*cism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Witty</er>.]</ety> <def>A witty saying; a sentence or phrase which
is affectedly witty; an attempt at wit; a conceit.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He is full of conceptions, points of epigram, and
<qex>witticisms</qex>; all which are below the dignity of heroic
verse.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wittified</ent>⟦br⟧
